'''Herbaspirillum lusitanum''' is a [[nitrogen-fixing]] [[betaproteobacteria]] from the genus [[Herbaspirillum]] with was found in [[root nodules]] of Common bean ([[Phaseolus vulgaris]]).<ref name="Valverde2003">{{cite journal |title = Herbaspirillum lusitanum sp. nov., a novel nitrogen-fixing bacterium associated with root nodules of Phaseolus vulgaris |author = Angel Valverde, Encarna Vel<U+00E1>zquez, Carmen Guti<U+00E9>rrez, Emilio Cervantes, Antonio Ventosa and Jos<U+00E9>-Mariano Igua |doi = 10.1099/ijs.0.02677-0 |journal = IJSEM |date = November 2003 |volume = 53 |pages 1979-1983 |url = http://ijs.sgmjournals.org/content/53/6/1979.abstract}}</ref> [[Phylogenetic]] analysis have shown that this bacteria belongs to the genus of Herbaspirillum.<ref name="Valverde2003"/> ''H. lusitanum'' hasn't got a [[Nif gene]]<ref name="Weissa_2012">{{cite journal |title = Draft Genome Sequence of Herbaspirillum lusitanum P6-12, an Endophyte Isolated from Root Nodules of Phaseolus vulgaris |author = Vin<U+00ED>cius Almir Weissa, Helisson Faoroa, Michelle Zibbetti Tadra-Sfeira, Roberto Tadeu Raittzb, Emanuel Maltempi de Souzaa, Rose Adele Monteiroa, Rodrigo Luis Alves Cardosoa, Roseli Wassema, Leda Satie Chubatsua, Luciano Fernandes Huergoa, Marcelo M<U+00FC>ller-Santosa, Maria Berenice Reynaud Steffensa, Liu Un Rigoa, F<U+00E1>bio de Oliveira Pedrosaa and Leonardo Magalh<U+00E3>es Cruza |doi = 10.1128/JB.00657-12 |journal = J. Bacteriol. |date = August 2012 |volume 194 |pages = 4136<U+2013>4137 |url = http://jb.asm.org/content/194/15/4136.full}}</ref> but a [[NodD-like gene]] is present but no [[Nod gene]]s wher found. The lack of nif and nod genes proposes that ''H. lusitanum'' is an opportunistic bacteria able of colonizing root nodules.<ref name="Weissa_2012"/> The miss of nif genes raises questions about the ability of ''H. lusitanum'' to fix nitrogen.<ref name="Weissa_2012"/>

